      "description": "<p>• A <strong>Deafened</strong> creature can’t hear and automatically fails any check that requires hearing.</p><p>• A <strong>Deafened</strong> creatures has a -10 penalty to their Perception.</p><p>• Creatures currently Hidden from a <strong>Deafened</strong> creature do not need to reroll Dexterity (Stealth) Checks to maintain Stealth against them.</p><p>• Wisdom based Checks, attacks and saving throws are made at disadvantage.</p><p>• A creature can willingly cover their ears for an extended period of time as a bonus action. Doing so imposes this Condition on them and occupies both hands until the beginning of their next turn.</p>",
